<TITLE> Saifur's remains reach Sylhet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com)The remains of M Saifur Rahman reached Sylhet on Monday afternoon for burial in the family graveyard in Moulavibazar. The ambulance carrying the coffin of the senior BNP leader reached Sylhet shortly after midday. Sylhet mayor Badaruddin Ahmed Kamran, Sylhet district BNP convener M Ilias Ali and metropolitan BNP president Shahriar Hossain Chowdhury received the coffin. The coffin was kept at Central Shaheed Minar for the public to pay their last respects, before a final namaj-e-janaza at the Shahi Eidgah was to be held at 1pm. BNP on Sunday demanded that the veteran leader should be buried with state honour. Secretary-general Khandaker Delwar Hossain made the demand to the government in a news conference at 11pm his old Dhaka house. Rahman's Qulkhwani will be held at Gulshan Azad Mosque on Friday after Asr prayers. Rahman, one of BNP senior-most leaders and Bangladesh's longest-serving finance minister, was killed in a car crash on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway on Saturday afternoon. Ruling and opposition members of parliament, family, friends, supporters and people from all walks of life paid tribute to the veteran politician in three separate namaj-e-janaza in the capital on Sunday. bdne
